{
  "page": "Corpse queen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">corpse queen</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Queen_of_North.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Queen of North.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e8/Queen_of_North.jpg/300px-Queen_of_North.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"378\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e8/Queen_of_North.jpg/450px-Queen_of_North.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e8/Queen_of_North.jpg/600px-Queen_of_North.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>The Queen of North, by wolverrain ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_King\" title=\"Night&#39;s King\">Night's King</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>corpse queen</b> was the legendary consort of <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_King\" title=\"Night&#39;s King\">Night's King</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Her given name is unknown.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corpse_queen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The corpse queen is said to have had cold, white skin and eyes like blue stars.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corpse_queen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Night%27s_King.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/87/Night%27s_King.png/300px-Night%27s_King.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"202\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/87/Night%27s_King.png/450px-Night%27s_King.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/87/Night%27s_King.png/600px-Night%27s_King.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Night%27s_King.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_King\" title=\"Night&#39;s King\">Night's King</a> makes love to his queen, by Curtana ©</div></div></div>\n<p>According to legend, <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_King\" title=\"Night&#39;s King\">Night's King</a> lived during the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>, not long after the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> was complete. He was a fearless warrior who served as the thirteenth <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>. After viewing the white-skinned woman from atop the Wall, he chased and loved her. Night's King brought her back to the <a href=\"/index.php/Nightfort\" title=\"Nightfort\">Nightfort</a> and after the unholy union, he declared himself king and her his queen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Night's King ruled the <a href=\"/index.php/Nightfort\" title=\"Nightfort\">Nightfort</a> as his own castle for thirteen years. During the dark years of his reign, horrific atrocities were committed, of which tales are still told in the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>. It was not until <a href=\"/index.php/Brandon_Stark_(Breaker)\" title=\"Brandon Stark (Breaker)\">Brandon the Breaker</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King of Winter</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Joramun\" title=\"Joramun\">Joramun</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/King-Beyond-the-Wall\" title=\"King-Beyond-the-Wall\">King-Beyond-the-Wall</a>, joined forces that Night's King was brought down and the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> freed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After his fall, when it was discovered that Night's King had been making sacrifices to the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a>, all records of him were destroyed and his very name was forbidden and forgotten.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">Maesters</a> are skeptical of the legend, thinking the corpse queen was possibly a daughter of a <a href=\"/index.php/Barrow_Kings\" title=\"Barrow Kings\">Barrow King</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Barrowlands\" title=\"Barrowlands\">barrowlands</a>, who were often associated with <a href=\"/index.php/Barrow\" title=\"Barrow\">graves and burials</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corpse_queen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Some reader theories associate the corpse queen with the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a> because of her description.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corpse_queen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A woman was <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_King\" title=\"Night&#39;s King\">his</a> downfall; a woman glimpsed from atop the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, with skin as white as the moon and eyes like blue stars. Fearing nothing, he chased her and caught her and loved her, though her skin was cold as ice, and when he gave his seed to her he gave his soul as well. He brought her back to the <a href=\"/index.php/Nightfort\" title=\"Nightfort\">Nightfort</a> and proclaimed her a queen and himself her king, and with strange <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">sorceries</a> he bound his <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Sworn Brothers</a> to his will.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> recalling <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Nan\" title=\"Old Nan\">Old Nan</a>'s stories</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corpse_queen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_56\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 56\">Chapter 56</a>, Bran IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_wall_and_beyond:_the_night.27s_watch.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Wall and Beyond: The Night's Watch.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403122226\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.153 seconds\nReal time usage: 2.308 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1199/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10706/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 7157/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1827/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3017/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.300/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.51 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00% 2284.857      1 -total\n 98.35% 2247.110      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 98.27% 2245.259      1 Template:Infobox\n  5.22%  119.316     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  1.37%   31.325      8 Template:Ref\n  1.11%   25.296      2 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.92%   21.062      8 Template:Ref/core\n  0.20%    4.623      1 Template:Quote\n  0.19%    4.382      1 Template:References\n  0.08%    1.941      2 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:23625-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403122223 and revision id 311483\n -->\n",
